CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1969, pg. 17 reads: "$1,000 Check - Everyone is all smiles as Milicka Club treasurer, Valerie Troy (left), hands a check for $1,000 to Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr., president, Pa. State Conference of NAACP, and Mrs. Alma Fox, executive secretary of the Pittsburgh Branch NAACP, while Milicka Club president Evelyn Brock and the club's sponsor, Ida Jones, look on. - All Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Milickas Civic Club member Valerie Troy presenting check for NAACP to Atty. Henry R. Smith Jr. and Alma Speed Fox, Evelyn Brock, and Ida Jones, posed in Rostraver Gardens for "Do Your Thing" Cabaret, Belle Vernon
